## Step 1: DSL Grammar Design

### DSL Language Overview

The language is named **CloudPol**. A policy file consists of one or more policy statements. Statements follow this pattern:

```
ALLOW | DENY  ROLE "<role_name>"  ACTION "<action>"
  ON RESOURCE "<resource>"
  [WHERE <condition_expr>];
```

### Formal BNF Grammar

```
<program>       ::= <statement>+

<statement>     ::= <effect> ROLE <STRING> ACTION <STRING>
                    ON RESOURCE <STRING>
                    [WHERE <condition>] SEMICOLON

<effect>        ::= ALLOW | DENY

<condition>     ::= <simple_cond>
                  | <simple_cond> AND <condition>
                  | <simple_cond> OR  <condition>
                  | NOT <simple_cond>

<simple_cond>   ::= <attribute> <rel_op> <value>

<attribute>     ::= ip | time | mfa | region | tag

<rel_op>        ::= == | != | < | > | <= | >=

<value>         ::= <STRING> | <NUMBER> | TRUE | FALSE

<STRING>        ::= '"' [^"]* '"'
<NUMBER>        ::= [0-9]+(\.[0-9]+)?
```

### Token Set

| Token | Pattern | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `KW_ALLOW` | `ALLOW` | Effect keyword |
| `KW_DENY` | `DENY` | Effect keyword |
| `KW_ROLE` | `ROLE` | Subject specifier |
| `KW_ACTION` | `ACTION` | Action specifier |
| `KW_ON` | `ON` | Resource preposition |
| `KW_RESOURCE` | `RESOURCE` | Resource specifier |
| `KW_WHERE` | `WHERE` | Condition clause |
| `KW_AND` | `AND` | Logical AND |
| `KW_OR` | `OR` | Logical OR |
| `KW_NOT` | `NOT` | Logical NOT |
| `KW_TRUE` | `TRUE` | Boolean literal |
| `KW_FALSE` | `FALSE` | Boolean literal |
| `KW_MFA` | `mfa` | MFA attribute |
| `KW_IP` | `ip` | IP attribute |
| `KW_TIME` | `time` | Time attribute |
| `KW_REGION` | `region` | Region attribute |
| `KW_TAG` | `tag` | Tag attribute |
| `OP_EQ` | `==` | Equality |
| `OP_NEQ` | `!=` | Inequality |
| `OP_LT` | `<` | Less than |
| `OP_GT` | `>` | Greater than |
| `OP_LEQ` | `<=` | Less-or-equal |
| `OP_GEQ` | `>=` | Greater-or-equal |
| `STRING` | `"..."` | Quoted string literal |
| `NUMBER` | `[0-9]+` | Numeric literal |
| `SEMICOLON` | `;` | Statement terminator |

