## Step 2: Lexical Analysis (Flex)

#### [NEW] [policy_lexer.l](file:///home/manthankhawse/cd-cp/src/policy_lexer.l)

Full Flex lexer. Handles:
- All keywords (case-sensitive)
- Quoted string literals with value capture
- Multi-character operators (`==`, `!=`, `<=`, `>=`)
- Line/column tracking for error reporting
- Single-line (`//`) and block (`/* */`) comments
- Whitespace skipping

#### [NEW] [policy_parser.y](file:///home/manthankhawse/cd-cp/src/policy_parser.y)

Bison stub that declares all tokens from the lexer so the lexer compiles cleanly. Full grammar rules come in Step 3.

#### [NEW] [ast.h](file:///home/manthankhawse/cd-cp/include/ast.h)

AST node type enum and struct declarations for use in later steps.

#### [NEW] [Makefile](file:///home/manthankhawse/cd-cp/Makefile)

Drives the build: `flex → bison → gcc` compilation chain.

